    "When T → 0 the most likely element (based on the CLM prediction) is selected as the next element of the sequence, while the higher the T, the more random the selections.",
    "T = 1 corresponds to using the CLM predictions as the sampling probability of each element at each generation step.",
    "We experimented with an increasing sampling temperatures (from T = 1.0 to T = 2.0 with a step of 0.25).",
    "Each T value was used to generate 10,240 SMILES strings per model across the five chosen targets and all training-test splits.",
    "Then, we evaluated the designs based on three metrics (Fig. 4): Fig."
